President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Kamala Shirin Lakhdhir as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Indonesia. Lakhdhir is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has previously served as Ambassador to Malaysia. She has also held various positions within the Department of State, including Executive Secretary and Executive Assistant to the Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs. Lakhdhir has extensive experience in Southeast Asia, including serving as U.S. Consul General in Belfast, Northern Ireland, and Director of the Office of Maritime Southeast Asian Affairs. She holds a B.A. from Harvard College and an M.S. from the National War College.

Additionally, President Biden intends to nominate John W. McIntyre as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Kingdom of Eswatini. McIntyre is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Minister-Counselor for Management Affairs at the U.S. Embassy in Jakarta, Indonesia. He has previously held positions in various embassies, including Deputy Chief of Mission in Kingston, Jamaica, and Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago. McIntyre has also worked in management and resource positions within the State Department. He holds a Bachelor's degree from the University of Wisconsin and a Master of Public Administration degree from the University of Kansas. McIntyre is married to Flora Zylfijaj and they have two children.